grund show — print one declaration's body by ID, so an agent pulls a single fact
into context without loading the whole document.

Usage:  grund show <ID>[.<section>] [PATH] [--section S] [--brief|--toc|--full] [--format text|md|json] [--path PATH]

Modes form an ordered ladder (each adds to the previous):
  --brief                heading + first paragraph    e.g. grund show --brief FS-login
  (default)              + the rest of the lead, cut at the first child section
  --toc                  + the nested section map     e.g. grund show --toc FS-login
  --full                 + every subsection body      e.g. grund show --full FS-login

Other options:
  --section S            show only that section path, e.g. --section 3.1
  --format text|md|json  text (default) is the body; md keeps the heading; json wraps it
  --path PATH            repo or subtree to resolve the ID in (default `.`)

Exit:  0 printed · 1 ID not found / ambiguous / broken stub / unknown section · 2 CLI error.

Examples:
  grund show FS-login              # the lead — the cheap default
  grund show FS-login --toc        # lead + section map
  grund show FS-login.3.1          # the lead of that nested section
  grund show FS-login --full       # the whole declaration body

ID not found? `grund list` shows every declared ID; `grund id <KIND> "…"` proposes a new one.
